# Result Types & Pattern Matching (Hard Rule)

- Fallible ops in `lib/` and `services/` return `Result<T, E>` (neverthrow): `ok(value)` / `err(error)`; no throwing in business logic.
- Call sites: use `.match({ ok, err })` or `isOk()`/`isErr()`; handle both paths. Use `ts-pattern` or `.match()` for discriminated unions; every case handled.

```ts
result.match({ ok: (v) => ..., err: (e) => ... });
```
